This paper deals with optimization and experimental design, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Bayesian optimization and submodular functions also suggests a focus on optimization and combinatorial algorithms. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the application of these techniques to biochemical engineering suggests a focus on computational biology and computational engineering, making cs.CE (Computational Engineering) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the use of submodular functions for optimization suggests a focus on discrete optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
